#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.125"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.125:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.125:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga"
msgstr "13. Kusināra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.125:0.3"
msgid "125. Gotamakacetiyasutta"
msgstr "125. The Gotamaka Tree-shrine"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.125:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati gotamake cetiye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Gotamaka Tree-shrine."

msgctxt "an3.125:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an3.125:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an3.125:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an3.125:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

# Cp. MN 77
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.125:2.1"
msgid "“Abhiññāyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desemi, no anabhiññāya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I teach based on direct knowledge, not without direct knowledge."

msgctxt "an3.125:2.2"
msgid "Sanidānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desemi, no anidānaṃ."
msgstr "I teach with reasons, not without them."

# I don’t understand BB’s problem here, see his note. Surely this just refers to the anusasanipatihariya, the demonstration of instruction. https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-miracles-and-demonstrations/4611
msgctxt "an3.125:2.3"
msgid "Sappāṭihāriyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desemi, no appāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr "I teach with a demonstrable basis, not without it."

msgctxt "an3.125:2.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, abhiññāya dhammaṃ desayato no anabhiññāya, "
"sanidānaṃ dhammaṃ desayato no anidānaṃ, sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desayato no "
"appāṭihāriyaṃ, karaṇīyo ovādo, karaṇīyā anusāsanī."
msgstr "Since this is so, you should follow my advice and instruction."

msgctxt "an3.125:2.5"
msgid ""
"Alañca pana vo, bhikkhave, tuṭṭhiyā, alaṃ attamanatāya, alaṃ somanassāya:"
msgstr "This is enough for you to feel joyful, delighted, and happy:"

msgctxt "an3.125:2.6"
msgid "‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto dhammo, suppaṭipanno saṃgho’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha! The teaching is well explained! "
"The Saṅgha is practicing well!’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.125:3.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "an3.125:3.2"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "an3.125:3.3"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne sahassī lokadhātu akampitthāti."
msgstr "And while this discourse was being spoken, the galaxy shook."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.125:3.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
